  "translations": {
    "en": "The adversary who claims against you: if his claim is true, witness against yourself, do not wrong him, give his due. If false, be gentle, show only kindness, do not displease your Lord. There is no strength save in Allah. Your adversary against whom you claim: if right, be polite; if wrong, fear Allah, repent, and abandon the claim. The one seeking advice: if he has good opinion, advise accordingly; if not, direct him to one who knows. The advisor: do not accuse him for differing opinion; if he agrees, praise Allah.",
